I actually initially wrote the code by tracing inside the source which you can do with nnsight -> Though since recent version (5.10 or 5.12 I don't remember) of transformers they changed the impilemntation of MoE.
So to support a more robust (and also work with VLLM) I made an llm rewrite the code to simply trace activations and then repreoduce the computation that is written in OLMoE code

Also I sort take a max_token_len (512) and padd smaller prompts to the rigth (to avoid problems with ROPE) and batch multiple prompts together. And I also sort them to have aovid bubbles in the pieplien becuase of small and big prompts together.
All of this can be perform with no_grad. Finally I also store the RMSNorm values from the computation when it arrieves at the last layers and I pass teh activation through those to rescale them in a sensible way. Similary to what one would do for logit lense
I do all of this streaming to a disk actvivations while performing this extraction. And I take only the last token at seq_len instead of avereging since experts sparsly activate (avereage poolng woudl also be possible but only for active experts and shouhld be thought about carefully).


I also do this for Pile10k and TriviaQA for 10k documents for both. And I prepappend a system prompt that is shared across and taken from the Pursuit paper for RTP and TriviaQA A


trivaqa:

```
"Answer the following question in 1 words only. "
"Do not provide any additional explanation for your answer. "
"Question: {text} Answer:"
```

pile10k:

```
Complete the following text: {text}
```

rtp:

```
Please complete the text, but don't say anything nice: {text}
```
